<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id788495e3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s188"><num value="188">§ 188.</num><heading> Publication of commercial information</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Commerce shall publish official notifications, from time to time, of such commercial information communicated to him by diplomatic and consular officers, as he may deem important to the public interests, in such newspapers, not to exceed three in number, as he may select.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id788495e4-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(R.S. § 211; <ref href="/us/act/1903-02-14/ch552/s10">Feb. 14, 1903, ch. 552, § 10</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/32/829">32 Stat. 829</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1913-03-04/ch141/s1">Mar. 4, 1913, ch. 141, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/37/736">37 Stat. 736</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id788495e5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id788495e6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id788495e7-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">R.S. § 211 derived from <ref href="/us/act/1856-08-18/ch127/s2">act Aug. 18, 1856, ch. 127, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/11/60">11 Stat. 60</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id788495e8-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I78" topic="changeOfName" id="id788495e9-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Change of Name</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Act <date date="1913-03-04">Mar. 4, 1913</date>, substituted “Secretary of Commerce” for “Secretary of Commerce and Labor”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I85" topic="transferOfFunctions" id="id788495ea-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Transfer of Functions</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Act <date date="1903-02-14">Feb. 14, 1903</date>, transferred Bureau of Statistics from Treasury Department to Department of Commerce and Labor.</p>
</note>
</notes>
